<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="63266792-091b-591c-91d1-35135594e21c" activityNameId="3ed12425-6c5d-4835-8b55-e3f0bd6f0be0" parentActivityId="786e18f6-35f3-48e1-ab47-66a6b5008c13" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">treatment of waste paint, sanitary landfill</activityName>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">The activity starts with the waste being available at the gate of the treatment facility. Collection and transportation of the waste to the treatment plant is not included.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">The activity ends with the waste being treated and waste-specific emissions from the landfill are released to the environment (air due to landfil gas, water due to landfil leachate, and subsequent into groundwater).</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the activity of waste disposal of 'waste paint' in a sanitary landfill. Recommended use of this dataset: For disposal of small amounts of dried paint, which go to disposal as part of a larger, burnable item or in small quantities. Larger amounts of waste paint, unused paint or removed (stripped) paint are to be disposed in hazardous waste incinerator. Inventoried waste consists of fraction: 100% paint (remains); . Waste composition (wet, in ppmw): gross heating value 10.86 MJ/kg; net heating value 10.14 MJ/kg; H2O na; O 290300; H 36288; C 651510; S na; N na; P na; B na; Cl 1600; Br na; F na; I na; Ag na; As 2.5; Ba na; Cd 5.0622; Co 388.23; Cr 1040.7; Cu 59; Hg 0.6; Mn na; Mo 38.619; Ni 15; Pb 15246; Sb na; Se na; Sn 256.78; V na; Zn 3251.5; Be na; Sc na; Sr na; Ti na; Tl na; W na; Si na; Fe na; Ca na; Al na; K na; Mg na; Na na. Share of carbon in initial waste waste that is biogenic 0%. Share of metals in waste not oxidised and bulk-recyclable (exclude very small or thin parts) Iron: 0%; Alu: 0%; Copper: 0%. Overall degradability of waste during 100 years: 1%. Landfill gas capture and utilisation generates 0.004939 kWh of electricity and 0.008908 MJ of useful heat. 0.001062 kg waste mass remains in the landfill even after the long term period.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="9a63625a-358b-4c1d-bf95-50ba038a759b">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">3821:Treatment and disposal of non-hazardous waste</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="f9221622-cc45-11de-98ed-0019e336be3a">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">Europe without Switzerland</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The site has mean annual temperature (MAT) of 10.403 degC, mean annual precipitation (MAP) of 960.474141305017 mm/year, and net infiltration of 510.400775481061 mm/year.The leachate percolating through the landfill has an average residence time of 9.8 years. References:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">UN data, 2020. Precipitation, Environment Statistics Database, United Nations Statistics Division Available at: http://data.un.org/Data.aspx?q=precipitation&amp;d=ENV&amp;f=variableID%3a6;</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">World Bank, 2022. Surface area (sq.km), World Bank Group Available at: https://data.worldbank.org/indicator/AG.SRF.TOTL.K2</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This is an inventory for a sanitary (controlled) landfill for municipal solid waste. Ultimate average landfill height is 20 meters. Operation phase duration is 30 years. The total raw landfill gas mass produced in the landfill from this waste is 0.009491 kg. The total CH4 mass in the raw landfill gas is 0.006322 kg. Percentage of landfill gas directly emitted is 47w%. Percentage of landfill gas captured and flared is 18.02w%. Percentage of landfill gas captured and utilised is 34.98%. Conversion efficiencies are 27.8e% for electricity and 13.5e% for useful heat.  Leachate collected during the first 100 years is collected and treated region-specifically before emission. Based on average waste composition and climate data the end of carbonate phase is estimated to be reached 4'389 years after waste deposition.</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="1994-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true"/>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
